            "answer_text": "You won\u2019t earn exactly what you\u2019d expect, but you might earn something. The royalty calculations are a lot more complicated than a straight up amount per stream. The thing though is that Spotify is pretty good at detecting fraudulent streaming scenarios, and if you played a song or album on repeat for a month, you\u2019d definitely get noticed. If it looked like you were just trying to cheat the system, you might get your user banned and the streams of your track zeroed out. For the record, we knew about Sleepify pretty quickly (Spotify employees are music fans, of course, and read the music blogs and track bands too). We let it go as long as we thought was reasonable. Even if we hadn\u2019t seen it on social media early on, we would have caught it soon when a band came out of nowhere tracking up a ton of repeat listenings on a single album. Spotify wouldn\u2019t let this happen again, most likely. ",
